       "link": "https://2e.aonprd.com/Feats.aspx?ID=2239",
       "description": "You've mastered useful spells that let you find hidden truths others might miss, and a preferred spell comes naturally to you. When you gain this feat, choose one of the innate spells granted by the  Lore Seeker  feat:  comprehend language ,  restore senses , or  see invisibility . You can cast this spell three times per day instead of once per day.  When you cast any of the spells granted by Lore Seeker as innate spells, they gain additional effects. When you cast  , the spell is heightened to 4th level. When you cast  , the spell is heightened to half your level, rounded up. When you cast  , for the duration of the spell you can use an action, which has the  concentrate  trait, to see invisible creatures normally (instead of seeing them as translucent shapes that are  concealed  to you) until the end of your next turn."
